102 hedit~
HEDIT
 
This command is specifically for immortals with security 9 to allow the
creation or modification of help files.
 
The following commands are used to edit and create help entries
 
{yhedit <command>{x - where command is the name of the help file you wish to edit
{ytext{x - will put you in the editor
{ynew <command>{x - will create a new help entry with the keyword command
{ydone{x - will exit the heditor
{ydelete{ - deletes the currently viewed help file
{ynivel <level>{x - will restrict access to the help file to a certain level range.
 
{BPlease note, hedit is very unstable. So please use {yasave changed{B before
using it{x
~

102 RENAME~
RENAME <character you wish to change> <new name>
 
This command is only available at level 109 and 110. It is used to change
the persons character name. It is an effective command to use for players
who have no knowledge of creating an acceptable roleplaying name and for
people who purposely create characters with unacceptable names, such as 
"Porky" "Ice-T" and so on and so forth.
~

102 GRAB~
Syntax: GRAB <item> <char>
 
This level 102 command is a very useful tool to use when someone has an
item in their inventory and you want to take it, for whatever purpose,
without having to force them to drop it or take your chances by stealing
it. What ever the item it is you wish to grab from a character, it MUST
be in that persons inventory. You can NOT grab items that are being worn
held or wielded. This a powerful command, please do not over abuse it by
grabing everything in a persons inventory, leaving them with nothing,
wondering and complaining that it all disappeared.
~

103 GUILD~
Syntax: GUILD <character> <clan name>
 
This skill may only be used by those at level 105. You may change a players
guild (clan) to whatever you may desire it to be changed to, without the
hassle of having to wait for a recruiter, leader or God of that particular
clan to show up to induct the person themself. Instead, using this command,
you'll be able to change a characters clan to any of the clans available
to choose from on the appropriate list.
 
'HELP LISTCLAN' will give you a current list of available guilds.
~

102 TRANSIN~
Syntax: TRANSIN <text>
 
This neat little command is mostly used in part for a better roleplaying
enviroment. Type the word TRANSIN followed by a text sentence. When you 
transfer someone into the same room as you or to anywhere you wish to,
everyone will see a message appear, almost like a sort of EMOTE. To 
everyone in the same room as the person, they will see, for example:
 
Schmuck has been summoned by a greater force!
 
Your TRANSIN in this case, would be 'has been summoned by a greater force'
Schmuck is the name of the character of which you transfered, there is no
need to add this into your TRANSIN, for the code automaticaly does that.
Everyones default transin is <name> arrives in a mushroom cloud. You may 
leave it or change it to your liking. In the example above, you'd simply
type TRANSIN has been summoned by a greater force. Fairly simple to use.
~

102 TRANSOUT~
Syntax: TRANSOUT <text>
 
Identical to TRANSIN, this will display a text to everyone in the room
when someone is transfered out. You may put in whatever suites your needs,
however, you must put in a verb as the first word of the text, a verb
which depicts a person leaving. Examples would be:
 
Disappears / sent back 
 
Those are just two of many you could come up with. For a better
understanding, also see 'HELP TRANSIN'.
~

