102 ORESET~
Syntax: ORESET <vnum> <args>
        -no_args               = into room
        -<obj_name>            = into obj
        -<mob_name> <wear_loc> = into mob                                      
 
This command MUST be used from inside REDIT. Once in REDIT and an object
has been created, you may then choose to load it into the resets for
the room you want it in or mob you want it on by using ORESET.
You must follow the ORESET with the VNUM of the object you wish to add.
Anything you add to a room's resets will continue to repop, given that
it has been removed from the room, so, if you use the ORESET command to
load an object for yourself, make sure to delete the reset immediately.
 
Type 'HELP RESET' for more information on using resets.
~

